{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper, thermal serving bowl or other large bowl","id":"r70570","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-BoaMOJw-jCU\/XZQHW3PBwvI\/AAAAAAAAcHg\/HzwdFKFNK7MnmN0eQRLqpaSM5CFnvbSzACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_hPxYFr5MJfFrdh_V.png","title":"Pad Thai noodles with prawns","publishedAt":"2014-07-22T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"20 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"200 g flat rice stick noodles"},{"content":"boiling water, for soaking"},{"content":"80 g roasted unsalted peanuts, for garnishing"},{"content":"3 garlic cloves"},{"content":"1 red chilli, deseeded if preferred"},{"content":"6 sprigs fresh coriander, roots and stems (reserve leaves for garnishing)"},{"content":"1 ½ tbsp fish sauce"},{"content":"40 g lime juice (approx. 2-3 limes)"},{"content":"1 tbsp tamarind paste"},{"content":"2 tbsp soy sauce"},{"content":"¼ tsp shrimp paste"},{"content":"3 tsp palm sugar (approx. 1 cm cube), grated"},{"content":"2 eggs"},{"content":"500 g water"},{"content":"350 g raw prawns, peeled"},{"content":"70 g bean shoots, for garnishing"},{"content":"10 fresh chives, finely chopped, for garnishing"},{"content":"3 tbsp fried shallots, for garnishing"},{"content":"1 lime, cut into wedges, to serve"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"29 g","fat":"17.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"17.3 g","calories":"1480 kJ \/ 352 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Line both Varoma dish and tray with a piece of wet, well-wrung baking paper. Lightly grease the baking paper on Varoma tray and set aside."},{"content":"Soak rice stick noodles in boiling water as per packet instructions. Drain noodles and place into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl to keep warm."},{"content":"Place peanuts into mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place garlic, chilli and coriander roots and stems into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add 20 g olive oil and cook <b>1 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer half of the garlic-herb mixture into Varoma dish and set aside. Retain other half in mixing bowl."},{"content":"Add fish sauce, lime juice, tamarind paste, soy sauce, shrimp paste and palm sugar and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer sauce into thermal serving bowl or other large bowl with the drained noodles and combine with spatula until noodles are coated. Re-cover noodles and set aside to keep warm."},{"content":"Without cleaning mixing bowl, place eggs into mixing bowl and beat <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Transfer egg onto lined Varoma tray, and spread evenly to create a thin layer. Set Varoma tray carefully aside."},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl and place Varoma dish with garlic-herb mixture into position. Weigh prawns into Varoma dish, then stir gently stir to combine with spatula."},{"content":"Carefully insert Varoma tray with egg, then secure Varoma lid and steam <b>6 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Check prawns and transfer any cooked prawns to thermal serving bowl or other large bowl."},{"content":"Secure Varoma lid, then steam for a further <b>5-7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>, or until both egg and prawns are cooked to your liking."},{"content":"Remove Varoma tray with omelette. Slice omelette into thin strips then add omelette strips and prawns to thermal serving bowl or other large bowl with the noodles and combine."},{"content":"Top Pad Thai with bean shoots, chives, coriander leaves, fried shallots and reserved chopped peanuts. Serve immediately with lime wedges on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Vegetarian option<\/strong>: substitute prawns with 350 g mushrooms, sliced in step 8 and remove shrimp paste and fish sauce from recipe. Proceed as per recipe.","Shrimp paste, also known as belachan, can be found in Asian supermarkets."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","30m","4 portions"]}